content: Visited a local tech meetup. Met a developer who's into Rust. We're planning to collaborate on optimizing my trading algorithms. Learning Rust might give me that edge I need.
First job interview since I'm back. Discussed my AI trading strategies. They're intrigued by my approach, but it's back to the drawing board for some more refining.
Diving deeper into smart contracts. Wrote my first contract in Solidity. The potential to automate trading decisions with DeFi is mind-blowing. This could revolutionize my strategy.
Set up a risk management framework. Reflecting on past losses, I realized the importance of stop-loss orders. Starting to incorporate these into my AI models.
Got feedback from my mentor on my trading bot. He pointed out some inefficiencies in the data processing. Back to the code, but the mentorship is invaluable.
Went to a DeFi hackathon. Met some brilliant minds. We're brainstorming a project that integrates AI with smart contracts. It's exciting but challenging to keep up.
Struggled with a bug in my Rust code today. It's frustrating, but it's teaching me the nuances of memory safety. This is where I grow as a programmer.
Had a breakthrough with my trading strategy. By integrating sentiment analysis from social media, my AI model now predicts market movements with higher accuracy. Small wins.
Joined a study group for smart contract development. Learning from peers accelerates my understanding of blockchain. This community is my new support system.
Secured another job interview. This time, I'll pitch my AI-enhanced trading strategies with confidence. The market's response to my work has been encouraging.
Refined my risk management approach. Implemented automated stop-losses and position sizing based on volatility. This should prevent those devastating losses.
The trading bot is now live. Watching it execute trades based on my AI insights is surreal. It's not perfect, but it's learning, just like me.
Wrapping up a multi-day coding session. My Rust trading algorithm is now faster and more efficient. It's time to let it loose in the wild and see how it performs.
